Package org.parboiled.support

Class Summary
CanMatchEmptyVisitor<V> A MatcherVisitor determining whether a matcher can legally succeed with an empty match.
Characters An immutable, set-like aggregation of (relatively few) characters that allows for an inverted semantic ("all chars except these few").
Checks Utility methods for grammar integrity checks.
DefaultMatcherVisitor<V,R> A basic MatcherVisitor implementation that delegates all visiting methods to one default value method.
FollowMatchersVisitor<V> Collects the matchers that can legally follow the currently running matcher according to the grammar into a given list.
GetAStarterCharVisitor<V> Returns the first character a given matcher can start a match with.
InputBuffer Simple immutable wrapper around a char[] buffer providing basic access methods.
InputLocation (Almost) immutable descriptor for a certain position in an InputBuffer.
IsSingleCharMatcherVisitor<V> A MatcherVisitor determining whether a matcher is a basic single character matcher.
IsStarterCharVisitor<V> A MatcherVisitor determining whether a matcher can start a match with a given char.
LabelPrefixPredicate<V> A simple Node predicate determining whether a Node matches a given label prefix.
MatcherPath<V> Holds a snapshot of the current Matcher stack at a certain point during the parsing process.
NodeFormatter<V> A simple Formatter that provides String representation for parse tree nodes.
ParseTreeUtils General utility methods for operating on parse trees.
ParsingResult<V> A simple container encapsulating the result of a parsing run.
StringVar Simple specialization of a Var for Strings.
ToStringFormatter<T> A simple Formatter falling back to the objects toString() method.
Var<T> This class provides a "local variable"-like construct for action expressions in parser rule methods.
